==English==
===Pronunciation===
*Verb form: kro͝okt, /krʊkt/, /<tt>krUkt</tt>/
*Adjective: kro͝ok'ĭd, /ˈkrʊkɪd/, /<tt>"krUkId</tt>/

===Verb form===
'''crooked'''

#Past tense and [[past participle]] of '''to [[crook]]'''.

===Adjective===
'''crooked''' ({{compar}} '''more crooked''', {{superl}} '''most crooked''')

#not [[straight]]; having one or more [[bend]]s or [[angle]]s
#:''We walked up the crooked path to the top of the hill.''
#set at an angle; not vertical or square
#:''That picture is crooked - could you straighten it up for me?''
#(''figurative'') [[dishonest]] or [[illegal]]
#:''He was trying to interest me in another one of his crooked deals.''

